      <scopecontent id="aspace_77d85747c7b13559dbb399a58b0c179d">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Gordon James Collection consists of three albums of photographs taken in South Africa, 1900-1905. They show early mining operations (presumably for copper) in Tsumeb, Guchab, and Asis, 1900-1901; and scenery, daily life, and game animals. It is not clear whether James took the photographs himself.</p>
      </scopecontent>
